<br>
Eventually, another group pulled a large train and while we tried to stay and fight, it was soon obvious that we could not handle it.  Five of us ran for the zone, leaving the pally sitting in the basement, seemingly oblivious.<br>
<br>
T'wasn't a minute later than we saw her in groupchat saying, &quot;What the hell! Where is everyone!?!&quot; etc.  Around that time, the train musta wandered back down the basement because we saw her hightailing it out as we were coming back in, a new train behind her.  Good thing the druid re-SoW'ed her as we left!<br>
<br>
She told us that she'd been working late that week and hadn't gotten a lot of sleep for the past couple o' days, but wanted to play EQ anyway that night.<br>
<br>
Heh.  Still makes me laugh when I think about that and what she musta thought when she finally woke. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'm sure there are other funny stories like this one.  C'mon!  Share 'em!<br>
<br>
Kenai<br>
